@jpic Ahhh I found out - Sorry for wasting your time! I'm not sure where I got this code (probably following some online tutorials a long time ago), but there were these lines in my views.py:

```
# auto complete
class CountryAutocomplete(autocomplete.Select2QuerySetView):
    def get_queryset(self):
        # Don't forget to filter out results depending on the visitor !
        # if not self.request.user.is_authenticated():
        #     return Country.objects.none()

        qs = Country.objects.all()

        if self.q:
            qs = qs.filter(name__istartswith=self.q)

        return qs


class CityAutocomplete(autocomplete.Select2QuerySetView):
    def get_queryset(self):
        # if not self.request.user.is_authenticated():
        #     return Country.objects.none()

        qs = City.objects.all()


        FromCountry = self.forwarded.get('FromCountry', None)
        ToCountry = self.forwarded.get('ToCountry', None)

        if FromCountry:
            qs = qs.filter(country=FromCountry)
        elif ToCountry:
        	qs = qs.filter(country=ToCountry)
        if self.q:
            qs = qs.filter(name__istartswith=self.q)

        return qs
```

So yes, it is actually filtering 'name' with 'startswith'... It has been so long I didn't remember how I implemented this in the beginning. Thanks for looking at it and sorry for bothering you!

